t2     = Mcgeoch\n| title     = Invasion!: Operation Sea Lion, 1940\n| url       = https://books.google.com/books?id=fHQABAAAQBAJ&pg=PT87\n| date      = 10 July 2014\n| publisher = Taylor & Francis\n| isbn      = 978-1-317-86827-9\n}}\n*{{cite book\n|last=Fest\n|first=Joachim C.\n|authorlink=Joachim Fest\n|title=Hitler\n|publisher=Verlagg Ulstein\n|year=1973\n|isbn=0-15-602754-2\n|url-access=registration\n|url=https://archive.org/details/hitler00joac}}\n* {{cite book\n| last       = Fleming\n| first      = Peter\n| authorlink = Peter Fleming (writer)\n| title      = Operation Sea Lion\n| url       = https://archive.org/details/operationsealion00flem\n| url-access = registration\n| publisher  = Simon & Schuster\n| year       = 1957\n}} {{ISBN|0-330-24211-3}}\n* {{cite book\n| last      = Forczyk\n| first     = Robert\n| title     = We march against England: Operation Sea Lion 1940-41\n| publisher = Ospsrey\n| year      = 2016\n}}\n* Greiner, H. 'Operation Seelowe and Intensified Air Warfare Against England up to 30 October 1940', in Detweiler, D. ''World War II German Military Studies'', Volume 7 of 24 (New York, 1979)\n* {{cite book\n| last      = Haining\n| first     = Peter\n| title     = Where the Eagle Landed: The Mystery of the German Invasion of Britain, 1940\n| publisher = Robson\n| year      = 2004\n}} {{ISBN|1-86105-750-4}}\n* {{cite book\n| last      = Hewitt\n| first     = Geoff\n| title     = Hitler's Armada: The Royal Navy and the Defence of Great Britain, April \u2013 October 1940\n| publisher = Pen & Sword Maritime\n| year      = 2008\n}} {{ISBN|978-1844157853}}\n* {{cite book\n| last      = Hewitt\n| first     = Nick\n| title     = Coastal Convoys 1939\u20131945: The Indestructible Highway\n| publisher = Pen & Sword Maritime\n| year      = 2008\n}} {{ISBN|978-1-84415-861-4}}\n*{{cite book\n|last=Hildebrand\n|first=Klaus\n|authorlink1=Klaus Hildebrand\n|title=The Foreign Policy of the Third Reich\n|url=https://archive.org/details/foreignpolicyoft0000h