aniards and Indians in Colonial Oaxaca |location= Norman, OK |publisher=University of Oklahoma Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Cline |first=S.&nbsp;L. |year=1991 |chapter=A Cacicazgo in the Seventeenth Century: The Case of Xochimilco |title=Land and Politics in the Valley of Mexico |editor=H.&nbsp;R. Harvey |location= Albuquerque, NM |publisher= University of New Mexico Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Coatsworth |first=John H. |year=1998 |chapter=Economic and Institutional Trajectories in Nineteenth-Century Latin America |title=Latin America and the World Economy since 1800 |editor=John H. Coatsworth |editor2=Alan M. Taylor |location=Cambridge, MA |publisher=David Rockefeller Center for Latin American Studies, Harvard University |ref=harv }}\n*{{cite book |last=Cutter |first=Charles R. |year=1995 |title=The Legal Culture of Northern New Spain, 1700\u20131810 |url=https://archive.org/details/legalcultureofno0000cutt |url-access=registration |location= Albuquerque, NM |publisher= University of New Mexico Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Deans-Smith |first=Susan |year=1992 |title=Bureaucrats, Planters, and Workers: The Making of the Tobacco Monopoly in Bourbon Mexico |location=Austin, TX |publisher=University of Texas Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Farriss |first=Nancy |authorlink= Nancy Farriss |year=1984 |title=Maya Society under Colonial Rule: The Collective Enterprise of Survival |url=https://archive.org/details/mayasocietyunder00farr |url-access=registration |location= Princeton, NJ |publisher= Princeton University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Foster |first=Lynn V. |year=2000 |title=A Brief History of Central America |location=New York, NY |publisher=Facts on File |isbn=0-8160-3962-3 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Gerhard |first=Peter |year=1993 |title=The Historical Geography of New Spain |edition=2nd |location=Norman, OK |publisher=University of Oklahoma Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Gibson |first=Charles |year=1952 |title=Tlaxcala in the Sixteenth Century |location=New Haven, CT |publisher=Yale University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Gibson |first=Charles |year=1964 |title=The Aztecs Under Spanish Rule: a History of the Indians of the Valley of Mexico, 1519\u20131810 |url=https://archive.org/details/aztecsunderspani00gibs |url-access=registration |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Gonzales |first=Phillip B. |year=2003 |title=Struggle for survival: the Hispanic land grants of New Mexico, 1848\u20132001 |journal=[[Agricultural History (journal)|Agricultural History]] |volume=77 |issue=2 |pages=293\u2013324 |jstor=3744837 |ref=harv|doi=10.1525/ah.2003.77.2.293 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Guti\u00e9rrez Brockington |first=Lolita |year=1989 |title=The Leverage of Labor: Managing the Cort\u00e9s Haciendas of Tehuantepec, 1588\u20131688 |location=Durham, NC |publisher=Duke University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Hamnett |first=Brian R. |year=1971 |title=Politics and Trade in Southern Mexico 1750\u20131821 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Haring |first=Clarence Henry |year=1947 |title=The Spanish Empire in America |location=New York, NY |publisher=Oxford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Hirschberg |first=Julia |year=1979 |title=Social experiments in New Spain: a prosopographical study of the early settlement at Puebla de Los Angeles, 1531\u20131534 |journal=Hispanic American Historical Review |volume=59 |issue=1 |pages=1\u201333 |jstor=2514134 |ref=harv|doi=10.2307/2514134 }}\n*{{cite book |last=von Humboldt |first=Alexander |authorlink=Alexander von Humboldt |year=1811 |title=Political Essay on the Kingdom of New Spain |location=Paris |publisher=F. Schoell |language=fr |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Hunt |first=Marta Espejo Ponce |year=1976 |chapter=The Processes of the Development of Yucatan, 1600\u20131700 |editor=Ida Altman |editor2=James Lockhart |title=The Provinces of Early Mexico: Variants of Spanish American Regional Evolution |location=Los Angeles, CA |publisher=UCLA Latin American Center |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Israel |first=Jonathan I. |year=1975 |title=Race, Class, and Politics in Colonial Mexico |location=New York, NY |publisher=Oxford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Jackson |first=Robert H. |year=1994 |title=Indian Population Decline: the Missions of Northwestern New Spain, 1687\u20131840 |location=Albuquerque, NM |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Lewis |first=Leslie |year=1976 |chapter=In Mexico City's Shadow: Some Aspects of Economic Activity and Social Processes in Texcoco, 1570\u20131620 |title=The Provinces of Early Mexico'', James Lockhart and Ida Altman, eds. Los Angeles |publisher=UCLA Latin American Center Publications |pages=125\u2013136 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Liss |first=Peggy K. |year=1975 |title=Mexico Under Spain: Society and the Origins of Nationality |location=Chicago, Illinois |publisher=University of Chicago Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Lockhart |first=James |year=1976 |chapter=Introduction |title=The Provinces of Early Mexico |location=Los Angeles, CA |publisher=UCLA Latin American Center |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Lockhart |first=James |year=1991 |chapter=Trunk lines and feeder lines: The Spanish Reaction to American Resources |editor=James Lockhart |title=Of Things of the Indies: Essays Old and New in Early Latin American History |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Lockhart |first=James |year=1992 |title=The Nahuas After the Conquest: A Social and Cultural History of the Indians of Mexico, Sixteenth Through Eighteenth Centuries |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |editor1-last=Lockhart |editor1-first=James |editor2-first=Ida |editor2-last=Altman |year=1976 |title=The Provinces of Early Mexico |location=Los Angeles, CA |publisher=UCLA Latin American Center |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Lockhart |first1=James |first2=Stuart |last2=Schwartz |year=1983 |title=Early Latin America |url=https://archive.org/details/earlylatinameric00lock |url-access=registration |location=New York, NY |publisher=Cambridge University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Lombardi |first1=Cathryn L. |first2=John V. |last2=Lombardi |first3=K. Lynn |last3=Stoner |year=1983 |title=Latin American History: a Teaching Atlas |url=https://archive.org/details/latinamericanhis0000lomb |url-access=registration |location=Madison, WI |publisher=University of Wisconsin Press |isbn=0-299-09714-5 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Marichal |first=Carlos |year=2006 |chapter=Mexican Cochineal and the European Demand for American Dyes, 1550\u20131850 |title=From Silver to Cocaine: Latin American Commodity Chains and the Building of the World Economy, 1500\u20132000 |editor=Steven Topik |editor2=Carlos Marichal |editor3=Zephyr Frank |location=Durham, NC |publisher=Duke University Press |pages=76\u201392 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=McCaa |first=Robert |year=2000 |chapter=The peopling of Mexico from origins to revolution |pages=241\u2013304 |editor=Michael R. Haines |editor2=Richard H. Steckel |publisher=Cambridge University Press |title=A Population History of North America |chapter-url=http://www.hist.umn.edu/~rmccaa/mxpoprev/cambridg3.htm |isbn=9780521496667 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Monsiva\u00eds |first=Carlos |year=1992 |chapter='Just Over That Hill'\": Notes on Centralism and Regional Cultures |editor=Eric Van Young |title=Mexico's Regions |publisher=Center for U.S.-Mexican Studies, UCSD |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=de la Mota Padilla |first=Mat\u00edas |year=1870 |origyear=1742 |title=Conquista del Reino de Nueva Galicia en la Am\u00e9rica Septrentrional..., Texas, Sonora, Sinaloa, con noticias de la California |trans-title=Conquest of the Kingdom of New Galicia in North America..., Texas, Sonora, Sinaloa, with news of California |language=Spanish |url=http://hdl.loc.gov/loc.hisp/espbnms.0006 |location=Mexico |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Navarro y Noriega |first=Fernando |year=1820 |title=Report on the population of the kingdom of New Spain |location=Mexico |publisher=Office of D. Juan Bautista de Arizpe |language=Spanish |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Ouweneel |first=Arij |year=1997 |title=Shadows over Anahuac: an Ecological Interpretation of Crisis and Development in Central Mexico, 1730\u20131800 |location=Albuquerque, NM |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Reed |first=Nelson A. |year=1964 |title=The Caste War of Yucatan |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Restall |first=Matthew |year=1997 |title=The Maya World: Yucatec Culture and Society, 1550\u20131850 |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Restall |first=Matthew |year=2009 |title=The Black Middle: Africans, Mayas, and Spaniards in Colonial Yucatan |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Robinson |first=William Wilcox |year=1979 |title=Land in California: the story of mission lands, ranchos, squatters, mining claims, railroad grants, land scrip and homesteads |url=https://archive.org/details/landincalifornia00robi |url-access=registration |publisher=University of California Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Rojas Rabiela |first=Teresa |year=1991 |chapter=Ecological and Agricultural Changes in the Chinampas of Xochimilco-Chalco |title=Land and Politics in the Valley of Mexico |editor=H.&nbsp;R. Harvey |location=Albuquerque, NM |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |pages=275\u2013290 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Salvucci |first=Richard |year=1987 |title=Textiles and Capitalism in Mexico: An Economic History of the Obraje |location=Princeton, NJ |publisher=Princeton University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Sanchez |first1=Joseph P. |first2=Robert L. |last2=Spude |year=2013 |title=New Mexico: A History |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Shafer |first=Robert J. |year=1958 |title=The Economic Societies in the Spanish World, 1763\u20131821 |url=https://archive.org/details/economicsocietie0000shaf |url-access=registration |location=Syracuse, NY |publisher=Syracuse University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=de Sol\u00eds |first=Antonio |year=1771 |title=Historia de la conquista de M\u00e9xico, poblacion y progresos de la Am\u00e9rica Septentrional, conocida por el nombre de Nueva Espa\u00f1a |language=Spanish |location=Barcelona |publisher=Thomas Piferrer |url=https://archive.org/details/historiadelaconq01sols |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Spicer |first=Edward H. |year=1962 |title=Cycles of Conquest: The Impact of Spain, Mexico, and the United States on the Indians of the Southwest, 1533\u20131960 |url=https://archive.org/details/cyclesofconquest00spic |url-access=registration |location=Tucson, AZ |publisher=University of Arizona Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Szewczyk |first=David M. |year=1976 |chapter=New Elements in the Society of Tlaxcala, 1519\u20131618 |title=The Provinces of Early Mexico |editor=James Lockhart |editor2=Ida Altman |location=Los Angeles, CA |publisher=UCLA Latin American Center Publications |pages=137\u2013154 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Thomson |first=Guy P.&nbsp;C. |year=1989 |title=Puebla de Los Angeles: Industry and Society in a Mexican City, 1700\u20131850 |publisher=Westview Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Tovell |first=Freeman M. |year=2008 |title=At the Far Reaches of Empire: the Life of Juan Francisco De La Bodega Y Quadra |publisher=University of British Columbia Press |isbn=978-0-7748-1367-9 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E8_LXicsIlEC |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Tutino |first=John |year=1979 |chapter=Life and Labor on North Mexican Haciendas |editor=Elsa Cecilia Frost |display-editors=etal |title=El trabajo y los trabajadores en la historia de M\u00e9xico |publisher=El Colegio de M\u00e9xico y University of Arizona Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Tutino |first=John |year=1986 |title=From Insurrection to Revolution: Social Bases of Agrarian Violence 1750\u20131940 |location=Princeton, NJ |publisher=Princeton University Press |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Van Young |first=Eric |year=2006 |chapter=Introduction to the 25th Anniversary Edition |title=Hacienda and Market in Eighteenth-Century Mexico |edition=2nd |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Weber |first=David J. |year=1992 |title=The Spanish Frontier in North America |publisher=Yale University Press |isbn=0300059175 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Zeitlin |first=Judith Francis |year=1989 |title=Ranchers and Indians on the Southern Isthmus of Tehuantepec |journal=[[Hispanic American Historical Review]] |volume=69 |issue=1 |pages=23\u201360 |ref=harv|doi=10.2307/2516162 |jstor=2516162 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Zeitlin |first=Judith Francis |year=2005 |title=Cultural Politics in Colonial Tehuantepec: Community and State among the Isthmus Zapotec, 1500\u20131750 |location=Stanford, CA |publisher=Stanford University Press |ref=harv}}\n\n===Historiography===\n* Hanke, Lewis. ''Do the Americas Have a Common History?  A Critique of the Bolton Theory'' (1964)\n* Hurtado, Albert L. \"Bolton and Turner: The Borderlands and American Exceptionalism.\" ''Western Historical Quarterly'' 44#1 (2013): 4\u201320. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/westhistquar.44.1.0004 online]\n* Hurtado, Albert L. ''Herbert Eugene Bolton: Historian of the American Borderlands'' (University of California Press; 2012) 360 pages\n*{{cite book |last=Van Young |first=Eric |year=1992 |chapter=Are Regions Good to Think? |editor=Eric Van Young |title=Mexico's Regions |publisher=Center for U.S.-Mexican Studies, UCSD |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |editor-last=Weber |editor-first=David. J. |year=1991 |title=The Idea of the Spanish Borderlands |location=New York, NY |publisher=Garland Publishers |ref=harv}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Ida Altman|Altman, Ida]] and [[James Lockhart (historian)|James Lockhart]], eds. ''The Provinces of Early Mexico'' (UCLA Latin American Center 1976)\n* Altman, Ida, Sarah Cline, and Javier Pescador, ''The Early History of Greater Mexico'' (Pearson 2003)\n* Bakewell, P.J. ''A History of Latin America'' (Oxford U.P., 1997)\n* Bethell, Leslie, ed. ''The Cambridge History of Latin America'' (Vols. 1\u20132. Cambridge UP, 1984)\n* Ca\u00f1eque, Alejandro. \"The Political and Institutional History of Colonial Spanish America\" ''History Compass'' (April 2013) 114 pp 280\u2013291, {{DOI|10.1111/hic3.12043}}\n* Collier, Simon. ''From Cortes to Castro: An Introduction to the History of Latin America, 1492\u20131973'' (1974)\n* Gibson, Charles. ''The Aztecs Under Spanish Rule: A History of the Indians of the Valley of Mexico, 1519\u20131810''. (Stanford University Press 1964).\n* Lockhart, James. ''The Nahuas After the Conquest'' (Stanford University Press)\n* Muldoon, James. ''The Americas in The Spanish World Order'' (1994)\n* Parry, J.H. ''The Spanish Seaborne Empire'' (1974)\n* Parry, J.H. ''The Spanish Theory of Empire in the Sixteenth Century'' (1974)\n* Stein, Barbara H., and Stanley J. Stein. '' Crisis in an Atlantic Empire: Spain and New Spain, 1808\u20131810'' (Johns Hopkins University Press; 2014) 808 pages.\n* Leibsohn, Dana, and Barbara E. Mundy, ''Vistas: Visual Culture in Spanish America'', 1520\u20131820. http://www.fordham.edu/vistas, 2015.\n\n{{div col end|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Viceroyalty of New Spain}}{{Library resources box}}\n\n*[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Mexico_spanish_provinces.html Worldstatesmen.org: Provinces of New Spain]\n*[http://www.mexconnect.com/mex_/travel/dpalfrey/dpcolonial1.html MEXICO'S COLONIAL ERA\u2014PART I: The Settlement of New Spain] at mexconnect.com\n*[http: